{"word":"H1777 - דִּין - dîyn - deen - With a straight course","slug":"H1777","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">דִּין</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>dîyn"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>deen"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>With a straight course"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D3;&#x05BC;&#x05D5;&#x05BC;&#x05DF;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05D3;&#x05BC;&#x05D9;&#x05DF; - d&#x0131;&#x0302;yn  du&#x0302;n</b> - <i>deen, doon</i><p/>A primitive root (compare <a href=\"#/H113\">H113</a>); to <i>rule</i>; by implication to <i>judge</i> (as umpire); also to <i>strive</i> (as at law): - contend, execute (judgment), judge, minister judgment, plead (the cause), at strife, strive."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1779\">H1779</a>, <a href=\"#/H1781\">H1781</a>, <a href=\"#/H1783\">H1783</a>, <a href=\"#/H1835\">H1835</a>, <a href=\"#/H1839\">H1839</a>, <a href=\"#/H1840\">H1840</a>, <a href=\"#/H1842\">H1842</a>, <a href=\"#/H3036\">H3036</a>, <a href=\"#/H4066\">H4066</a>, <a href=\"#/H4068\">H4068</a>, <a href=\"#/H4079\">H4079</a>, <a href=\"#/H4080\">H4080</a>, <a href=\"#/H4082\">H4082</a>, <a href=\"#/H4084\">H4084</a>, <a href=\"#/H4090\">H4090</a>, <a href=\"#/H4091\">H4091</a>, <a href=\"#/H4092\">H4092</a>, <a href=\"#/H7384\">H7384</a>"}]}